        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 2:23PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 223 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Road Forks, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Blinding heavy rain will lower visibilities. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured
objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lordsburg, Road Forks, Lordsburg Playa, and Shakespeare.

This includes Interstate 10 in New Mexico between mile markers 5 and
22.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
